OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FEvergrande and its founder 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Faccused of $78bn fraud     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Chinese property giant Evergrande and  
OL,6, its founder, Hui Ka Yan, have been     
OL,7, accused of inflating revenues by $78bn 
OL,8, (#61.6m) in the two years before the   
OL,9, firm defaulted on its debt.            
OL,11,FThe country's financial markets        
OL,12,Fregulator has fined the company's      
OL,13,Fmainland business Hengda Real Estate   
OL,14,F$583.5m.                               
OL,16,FMr Hui also faces being banned for life
OL,17,Ffrom China's financial markets.        
OL,19,FIn January, Evergrande was ordered to  
OL,20,Fliquidate by a Hong Kong court.        
